Now regarding the MLRS acq code: it applies no aberration correction, because 
it is applied to the input station to center of moon coordinates.

DTADT shouldn't have to be carried or computed in genprst. It seems to make 
about .5 nsec difference in the range at the horizon and ~1 near the zenith?


Aberration: " SEE MURRAY (1981) MON. NOTICES ROYAL AST. SOCIETY 195, 639-648."
Sun velocity needed for aberration can be computed in closed form w/ usno 
novas solsys3 routine.

Setting UT1C=0 in genpred resulted in error wrt standard run of 608->-624 nsec.
Current versions w/ proper UT1C give errors of 9 -> -36nsec h to h.

Problem was that the WOBBLEREC needs to be applies to BODY FIXED coordinates,
and need to be applied with negatice signs to xpole and ypole. Both USNO and 
our routines give the same results. Now we are down to 0 error near the 
horizon and 2 nsec difference at the meridian.


